Description: Handle of a possibly Thasian pottery transport amphora. Rectangular stamp; kantharos symbol.
Curator's comments: Only known from Petrie's drawing in his Journal, 1884-5, p.110, 38b. 38 as originally identified consists of two stamps, that on 1925,0119.492 and this.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.0036)
